<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-26T13:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-26T13:29:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1908</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-26T21:00:00+02:31"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                            1918, 9 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 30, 9.11
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>206. <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName> telegraphs me
                                copy of long note addressed to Chinese Government asking cessation
                                of harboring of <persName corresp="#p_SGG1">Semenov</persName> or
                                permission for Soviet troops to pursue him on Chinese territory.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName> requests my aid
                                in obtaining Chinese agreement. Have telegraphed American Minister,
                                Peking, for information but made no reply to <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName>. Has Department
                                instructions?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>